<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/116129-one-third-of-the-way-through-i-don-t-care">One-third of the way through. I don&#39;t care for the main character (Kovacs); this normally wouldn&#39;t be such a big deal except for the fact that the story is narrated in first person, so there is essentially no escaping from this socially inept detective character. I personally feel that this novel should have been narrated in third person, which would have offered more narrative flexibility. Anyone else feel this way?</a>
</div>
